Explanation:

- The route in routes/uploadRoutes.js registers a POST handler at '/' on a router which is mounted at /api/upload, so the endpoint is POST /api/upload.
- The handler uses multer to process a single file field named "image".
- On success the code does: res.status(200).send({ message: 'Image uploaded successfully', image: `/${req.file.path}` }), so the 200 response body is a JSON object with:
  - message: string
  - image: string (URL/path to the uploaded file)
- On error (any multer/fileFilter error or other), the code does: res.status(400).send({ message: err.message }), so the 400 response body is a JSON object with:
  - message: string (error message, e.g., "Images only!")

